In [84]:
#Lets find ]out confidence intervals for scores now.
#Confidence interval refers to the probability that a population parameter will fall between a set of values.
#Confidence level refers to the probability with which a sample will fall into the confidence interval
#The z score is the number of standard deviations by which the value of a raw score is above or below the mean value of what is being observed or measured. 
#In hypothesis testing, a critical value is a point on the test distribution that is compared to the test statistic to determine whether to reject the null hypothesis.
In [98]:
np.random.seed(10)
sample_size = 1000

#Collecting random samples and getting population means.
sample_math = np.random.choice(data["math score"],size = sample_size)
sample_math_mean = sample_math.mean()

sample_reading = np.random.choice(data["reading score"],size = sample_size)
sample_reading_mean = sample_reading.mean()

sample_writing = np.random.choice(data["writing score"],size = sample_size)
sample_writing_mean = sample_writing.mean()

#Z critical value for (95% confidence level)
z_critical = stats.norm.ppf(q = 0.95)  

#Standard deviation
pop_stdev_math = data['math score'].std()  
pop_stdev_reading = data['reading score'].std()
pop_stdev_writing = data['writing score'].std()  

#Finding out margin of interval
margin_of_error_math = z_critical * (pop_stdev_math/math.sqrt(sample_size)) 
margin_of_error_reading = z_critical * (pop_stdev_reading/math.sqrt(sample_size)) 
margin_of_error_writing = z_critical * (pop_stdev_writing/math.sqrt(sample_size)) 

#Confidence interval
confidence_interval_math = (sample_math_mean - margin_of_error_math,
                            sample_math_mean + margin_of_error_math) 

confidence_interval_reading = (sample_reading_mean - margin_of_error_reading,
                               sample_reading_mean + margin_of_error_reading) 

confidence_interval_writing = (sample_writing_mean - margin_of_error_writing,
                               sample_writing_mean + margin_of_error_writing) 


# Results
print("Confidence interval math:",end=" ")
print(confidence_interval_math)
print("True mean: {}".format(data['math score'].mean()))
print("**********")
print("Confidence interval reading:",end=" ")
print(confidence_interval_reading)
print("True mean: {}".format(data['reading score'].mean()))
print("**********")
print("Confidence interval writing:",end=" ")
print(confidence_interval_writing)
print("True mean: {}".format(data['writing score'].mean()))
print("**********")
print("The z-critial value for this confidence interval was:",z_critical)

#calculate the grade of all kids.
def grade(percentage, status):
  if status == 'Fail':
    return 'E'
  if(percentage >= 90):
    return 'O'
  if(percentage >= 80):
    return 'A'
  if(percentage >= 70):
    return 'B'
  if(percentage >= 60):
    return 'C'
  if(percentage >= 40):
    return 'D'
  else :
    return 'E'

from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder
# creating an encoder
le = LabelEncoder()

# label encoding for test preparation course
data['test preparation course'] = le.fit_transform(data['test preparation course'])

# label encoding for lunch
data['lunch'] = le.fit_transform(data['lunch'])

# label encoding for race/ethnicity
# we have to map values to each of the categories
data['race/ethnicity'] = data['race/ethnicity'].replace('group A', 1)
data['race/ethnicity'] = data['race/ethnicity'].replace('group B', 2)
data['race/ethnicity'] = data['race/ethnicity'].replace('group C', 3)
data['race/ethnicity'] = data['race/ethnicity'].replace('group D', 4)
data['race/ethnicity'] = data['race/ethnicity'].replace('group E', 5)

# label encoding for parental level of education
data['parental level of education'] = le.fit_transform(data['parental level of education'])

#label encoding for gender
data['gender'] = le.fit_transform(data['gender'])

# label encoding for pass_math
data['pass_math'] = le.fit_transform(data['pass_math'])

# label encoding for pass_reading
data['pass_reading'] = le.fit_transform(data['pass_reading'])

# label encoding for pass_writing
data['pass_writing'] = le.fit_transform(data['pass_writing'])

# label encoding for status
data['status'] = le.fit_transform(data['status'])

# label encoding for status
data['grades'] = le.fit_transform(data['grades'])
